  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThese endpoints trigger stack overflows when an SSZ body is sent:\r\n\r\n- `POST /eth/v1/beacon/blocks`\r\n- `POST /eth/v2/beacon/blocks`\r\n\r\nThe Lighthouse VC never uses these endpoints, so this issue only affects other validator clients. Vouch does not (yet) use them, but the Teku VC _does_\r\n\r\n## Workaround\r\n\r\nIf running Teku, use this flag with your VC:\r\n\r\n- `--beacon-node-ssz-blocks-enabled=false`\r\n\r\nThis will prevent the SSZ endpoint from being used and use JSON instead, which does not exhibit the bug.\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nLighthouse v4.6.0-rc.0\r\n\r\n## Additional Info\r\n\r\nTesting and debugging is ongoing in https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/pull/5079 and related PRs. The root cause seems to be something related to warp's future chaining.\r\n",
